tlaps-bench — third-party attributions
======================================

tlaps-bench itself is released under the MIT License (see LICENSE). The
benchmark is built from TLA+ specifications written by third parties; this file
records their provenance and the original copyright/license notices. In the
benchmark task copies, source comments are removed (so the task copies carry no
in-file license header); the protocols and proof obligations are unchanged.

Benchmark groups live under benchmark/auto-complete/ (proof completion) and
benchmark/synthesis-from-scratch/ (proof from scratch).


== Benchmark specifications ==

tlaplus/Examples  —  MIT  —  https://github.com/tlaplus/Examples
    Every benchmark group whose name is prefixed `tlaplus_examples_` (including
    tlaplus_examples_GermanProtocol, the German cache-coherence protocol).
    Two of these carry their own upstream attribution:
      - tlaplus_examples_TencentPaxos: the TPaxos specification from
        https://github.com/Starydark/Tencent-Paxos-TLA
      - tlaplus_examples_byihive: Copyright (c) 2018 Backyard Innovations
        Pte. Ltd., Singapore; author Santhosh Raju <santhosh@byisystems.com>.

OpenAddressing  —  MIT  —  benchmark group OpenAddressing
    By Markus A. Kuppe, from the mku-OA branch of https://github.com/lemmy/Examples
    (a fork of tlaplus/Examples). A linear-probing open-addressing hash table.

TLAPS distribution examples  —  BSD-2-Clause  —  https://github.com/tlaplus/tlapm
    The examples/ directory of the TLAPS (tlapm) distribution, by Leslie
    Lamport, Stephan Merz, Damien Doligez, and others. Benchmark groups:
    Allocator, AtomicBakery, Bakery, BubbleSort, ByzantinePaxos, Cantor,
    Consensus, Data, EWD840, Euclid, Paxos, Peterson, Record, SimpleMutex,
    SumAndMax, TeachingConcurrency, Two-Phase. (Euclid additionally includes a
    spec from Leslie Lamport's TLA+ Hyperbook; SumAndMax is the VSTTE 2010
    competition solution by Damien Doligez, Stephan Merz, and Leslie Lamport.)

ZooKeeper / Zab  —  benchmark groups ZooKeeper, ZooKeeper_LowLevel
    TLA+ specifications of ZooKeeper's Zab atomic-broadcast protocol and of the
    apache/zookeeper v3.7.0 implementation, from the Remix paper
    (arXiv:2409.14301, https://arxiv.org/abs/2409.14301). The Zab protocol is
    described in Junqueira, Reed, and Serafini, "Zab: High-performance broadcast
    for primary-backup systems" (DSN 2011); the modeled system is
    https://github.com/apache/zookeeper (Apache-2.0).

Ivy liveness examples  —  benchmark groups prefixed `ivy_examples_`
    TLA+ translations of liveness examples from the Ivy verification system
    (https://github.com/kenmcmil/ivy, examples/liveness/, MIT).

Anvil  —  benchmark group AnvilLock
    TLA+ model of the lock demo (src/tla_demo.rs) from the Anvil framework for
    building formally verified Kubernetes controllers.

etcd / Specula  —  benchmark group etcd_raft
    From the Specula etcd-raft reference model (https://github.com/specula-org),
    derived from the raft TLA+ specification in etcd
    (https://github.com/etcd-io/etcd). Copyright 2024 The etcd Authors;
    licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0
    (http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0).

AbstractRaft  —  benchmark group AbstractRaft
    Contributed by Stephan Merz: a high-level TLA+ abstraction of the Raft
    consensus protocol (Diego Ongaro and John Ousterhout, "In Search of an
    Understandable Consensus Algorithm", USENIX ATC 2014).


== Bundled libraries ==

TLA+ CommunityModules  —  MIT  —  https://github.com/tlaplus/CommunityModules
    The etcd_raft group bundles copies of Folds, Functions, SequencesExt,
    FiniteSetsExt, BagsExt, Relation, and their *Theorems variants. (The full
    CommunityModules release and the TLA+ tools, tla2tools.jar, are downloaded
    at setup time and are not redistributed in this repository.)
